<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1126">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14592.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Garrett</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nuevo Laredo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Ricaut informed me this morning that he will probably be forced
                            to evacuate this city before many days and asked me to request
                            permission from the Department to cross his wounded and take them by
                            railroad through American territory to Matamoros.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>